Package: xtop
Version: 0.47.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 37740
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 v0.47.0 adds a full PHP-FPM per-site diagnostic — discovers every
 running php-fpm master via /proc, queries pm.status_path?full over
 each pool's listen socket, joins workers with /proc for live
 CPU/RSS/disk-I/O, then aggregates by docroot. Per-site panel shows:
 .
   - top client IPs with reverse-DNS + cloud-provider tag (AWS,
     Hetzner, OVH, DigitalOcean, Cloudflare, Tor, ~20 more)
   - hot URIs with scanner-probe markers (/.env, /legacy.php, etc.)
   - WHO HIT WHAT — top IP/URL combinations for IR triage
   - currently-running scripts (which app each worker serves)
   - filesystem scan: docroot walk for web-shell signatures + ELF binaries
   - slow-log analysis with BLOCKING PHP CALLS classified by severity
     (critical / heavy / normal), each with an optimization tip
   - ghost-site detection: vhost configured but docroot missing,
     with cleanup commands ready to paste
 .
 New RCA rules: phpfpm.webshell.suspect, phpfpm.bruteforce.detected,
 phpfpm.fs.webshell, phpfpm.fs.binary, phpfpm.vhost.stale,
 phpfpm.single_ip.dominant, phpfpm.5xx.surge, phpfpm.slow.high.
 .
 New TUI page (F8) with R = refresh, D = deep scan, j/k navigation
 and per-site detail mode. New cmd: xtop phpfpm with --site, --json,
 --max-ips, --deep-scan flags. The F7 per-process connections page
 has been removed.
 .
 PHP-FPM collector throttles to 30s refresh interval. FastCGI status
 fetch always runs (cheap ~2ms per pool); heavy docroot scans only
 on cold first walk or user-triggered deep scan.
